fields.description: The Ferrari California T was introduced to the US market in 2015 and was the first Ferrari to get the new 3.9 liter V8 twin-turbo engine that would eventually be shared with various models throughout Ferrari's lineup. It was the first Ferrari since the F40 to utilize a twin-turbo V8 engine. The California T was an evolution of the California in terms of styling and the most notable changes were to the exterior body. Rounded edges on the previous California were given a more angular look on the California T. Traditional horizontal exhaust pipes replaced the stacked exhaust pipes that came on the original California. The new engine, while smaller in displacement than the previous 4.3L V8, produces considerably more horsepower thanks to the twin turbochargers. It is rated at 553 horsepower and 557 Foot-Pounds of Torque. 0-60 mph takes as little as 3.3 seconds and the car carries a top speed of 196 mph. Car and Driver said, "The California T is more enthralling than its direct competitors, namely the Aston Martin DB9 and Bentley Continental GTC, and more passionate than the anodyne Porsche 911 Turbo S". The California T is an excellent grand tourer that can be enjoyed as a coupe or convertible thanks to its power retractable top. It makes a great daily driver and represents tremendous value especially since it comes with a 2 Year Certified Ferrari new Power Warranty.
